<HEADLINE>
WOMEN RIGHTS FOUNDATION LAUNCHES TAIWANESE WOMEN'S YEARBOOK
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei, May 2 (CNA) 05/02/07  21:47:29 (By Ruth Wang)
</P>
<P>
The Foundation for Women's Rights Promotion and Development held
a book launch and a seminar for its newly published "Taiwan Women
Yearbook--first edition" in Taipei City Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Many women's rights activists and representatives of women's
groups participated in the seminar Wednesday, held on the 10th
anniversary of the establishment of the Executive Yuan's
Commission on the Promotion of Women's Rights.
</P>
<P>
Su Chien-lin, convener of this yearbook's editing team, and
supervisor of the Taiwan Gender Equity Education Association,
said the yearbook recorded significant developments  and changes
in Taiwanese women's rights and gender equality, including
difficulties confronted and progress made by both the government
and women groups.
</P>
<P>
Three chapters of this book provide various useful references,
Vice Chairwoman of the Taiwan Research Institute, Lee An-ni said,
adding that the first chapter shows statistics of gender
differences collected in recent years that could be used as
policy making references by the government.
</P>
<P>
Chen Huei-hsin, chairwoman of the National Cheng Chi University's
Institute of Law and Inter-discipline, said the other two
chapters covers the government's efforts and achievements in
introducing legal regulations and policies relating to women's
rights over the past 10 years, and also introduces the role that
Taiwanese women groups have played in initiating gender related
issues and in supervising the government's policies in 2005.
</P>
